---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import AnimatedCard from "../../components/AnimatedCard.jsx";
---

<MainLayout title="My Progress">
  <AnimatedCard client:load>
    <div
      class="m-4 md:m-12 p-6 md:p-10 bg-white rounded-xl max-w-4xl w-full mx-auto text-gray-800 font-sans bg-opacity-70"
    >
      <div class="text-center">
        <h2
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900"
        >
          Follow The Journey: Live Progress
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center text-xl text-gray-500">
          During the ride in Sept/Oct 2026, this page will be the official hub
          to follow my progress in real-time. Check back daily for updates from
          the road!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12 items-start">
        <div class="lg:col-span-2">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            Live Location Map
          </h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Once the ride begins, this map will show my completed route for each
            day. You'll be able to see exactly which mountain pass I've climbed
            or which valley I'm riding through!
          </p>
          <div
            class="aspect-w-16 aspect-h-9 bg-gray-200 rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden"
          >
            <img
              src="/riding4gbs-atlantics2med.png"
              alt="The complete 1,685km route map for the Riding for GBS Pyrenean challenge."
              class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-8 px-4">
            <img
              src="/riding4gbs-atlantic2med-profile.png"
              alt="The complete elevation profile for the 1,685km Riding for GBS Pyrenean challenge."
              class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow-xl"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-gray-800 rounded-xl shadow-lg p-6 space-y-6 progress-panel"
        >
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-white">
            By the Numbers
          </h3>

          <div id="days-stat">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline mb-1">
              <span class="text-base font-medium text-gray-300 progress-label"
              ></span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-white progress-value"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="w-full bg-gray-600 rounded-full h-4">
              <div
                class="bg-blue-500 h-4 rounded-full progress-bar"
                style="width: 0%;"
              >
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div id="distance-stat">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline mb-1">
              <span class="text-base font-medium text-gray-300 progress-label"
              ></span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-white progress-value"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="w-full bg-gray-600 rounded-full h-4">
              <div
                class="bg-blue-500 h-4 rounded-full progress-bar"
                style="width: 0%;"
              >
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div id="climbing-stat">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline mb-1">
              <span class="text-base font-medium text-gray-300 progress-label"
              ></span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-white progress-value"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="w-full bg-gray-600 rounded-full h-4">
              <div
                class="bg-blue-500 h-4 rounded-full progress-bar"
                style="width: 0%;"
              >
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div id="funds-gbp-stat" class="pt-4">
            <div class="text-center">
              <span class="text-base font-medium text-gray-300 progress-label"
              ></span>
              <span
                class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-400 progress-value block"
              ></span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="funds-eur-stat" class="pt-2">
            <div class="text-center">
              <span class="text-base font-medium text-gray-300 progress-label"
              ></span>
              <span
                class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-400 progress-value block"
              ></span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-20">
        <hr class="my-16 border-gray-300 w-48 mx-auto" />
        <div class="text-center">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            Daily Ride Journal
          </h3>
          <p class="text-center text-lg text-gray-500 mb-8">
            Daily updates from the road will appear here once the challenge
            begins in September 2026!
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
          <div
            class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 opacity-50"
          >
            <img
              src="https://placehold.co/600x400/333/fff?text=Epic+Pyrenees+Photo"
              alt="View from the Tourmalet"
              class="w-full md:w-1/3 h-48 md:h-auto object-cover rounded-lg"
            />
            <div class="flex flex-col">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500">Day 10 of 21</p>
              <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
                To the Mediterranean
              </h4>
              <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed flex-grow">
                The final push to the sea! A day of rolling terrain and stunning
                coastal views as the Pyrenees faded behind me. The sense of
                achievement rolling into Collioure and seeing the Mediterranean
                was immense. Halfway point reached, and ready for a
                well-deserved rest. What an incredible first half of the
                challenge!
              </p>
              <a
                href="#"
                class="mt-4 text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline self-start"
                >View on Strava &rarr;</a
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
          <div
            class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 opacity-50"
          >
            <img
              src="https://placehold.co/600x400/333/fff?text=Epic+Pyrenees+Photo"
              alt="View from the Tourmalet"
              class="w-full md:w-1/3 h-48 md:h-auto object-cover rounded-lg"
            />
            <div class="flex flex-col">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500">Day 9 of 21</p>
              <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
                The Mighty Pailhères
              </h4>
              <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed flex-grow">
                The final push to the sea! A day of rolling terrain and stunning
                coastal views as the Pyrenees faded behind me. The sense of
                achievement rolling into Collioure and seeing the Mediterranean
                was immense. Halfway point reached, and ready for a
                well-deserved rest. What an incredible first half of the
                challenge!
              </p>
              <a
                href="#"
                class="mt-4 text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline self-start"
                >View on Strava &rarr;</a
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
          <div
            class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 opacity-50"
          >
            <img
              src="https://placehold.co/600x400/333/fff?text=Epic+Pyrenees+Photo"
              alt="View from the Tourmalet"
              class="w-full md:w-1/3 h-48 md:h-auto object-cover rounded-lg"
            />
            <div class="flex flex-col">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500">Day 8 of 21</p>
              <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
                The Recovery Roller
              </h4>
              <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed flex-grow">
                A shorter day, but no less picturesque. The rolling terrain
                offered a chance to recover the legs slightly after a big block
                of climbing, yet still kept me fully engaged. Ax-les-Thermes is
                a beautiful spot, a perfect transition before tomorrow's immense
                challenge. Every day is a gift on this journey.
              </p>
              <a
                href="#"
                class="mt-4 text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline self-start"
                >View on Strava &rarr;</a
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
          <div
            class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 opacity-50"
          >
            <img
              src="https://placehold.co/600x400/333/fff?text=Epic+Pyrenees+Photo"
              alt="View from the Tourmalet"
              class="w-full md:w-1/3 h-48 md:h-auto object-cover rounded-lg"
            />
            <div class="flex flex-col">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500">Day 7 of 21</p>
              <h4 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
                The Ariège Heights
              </h4>
              <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed flex-grow">
                Deep into the Ariège today, conquering the Col de Port and the
                stunning Port de Lers. These climbs are less famous but
                incredibly beautiful and challenging, with long, sustained
                gradients. The wildness of the landscape is incredible.
                Finishing in Tarascon-sur-Ariège, tired but fulfilled.
              </p>
              <a
                href="#"
                class="mt-4 text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline self-start"
                >View on Strava &rarr;</a
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </AnimatedCard></MainLayout
>
